caption;Versi 2
no;1
p;It was alone the Savior prayed
p;In dark Gethsemane;
p;Alone He drained the bitter cup
p;And suffered there for me.
empty
no;ref
pi;Alone, alone, He bore it all alone;
pi;He gave Himself to save His own,
pi;He suffered, bled and died alone, alone.
empty
no;2
p;It was alone the Savior stood
p;In Pilate’s judgment hall;
p;Alone the crown of thorns He wore
p;Forsaken thus by all.
empty
no;3
p;Alone upon the cross He hung
p;That others He might save;
p;Forsaken then by God and man
p;Alone, His life He gave.
